HEADWORD: Thiophenic
<hw>Thi`o*phen"ic</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <fld>(Chem.)</fld>
<def>Of, pertaining to, or derived from, thiophene; specifically,
designating a certain acid analogous to benzoic acid.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

